The paper deals with the problem of intrinsic image decomposition, which is a topic in computer vision and graphics. The use of CNNs for learning dense reflectance predictions suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of bilateral filtering and prior knowledge about reflectance constancy suggests that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the use of statistical dependencies and loss functions suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
